BIB                 10         24
TITLE       Multiplicity spectrometer for measuring neutron cross
            sections .
AUTHOR     (G.V.Muradyan, Yu.V.Adamchuk, Yu.G.Shchepkin,
           M.A.Voskanyan)
INSTITUTE  (4RUSKUR)
REFERENCE  (J,NSE,90,(1),60,1985)
MONITOR     The ratio of capture to fission detection efficiencies
            1.03 % was used to normalize the alpha value.
            Cf-252 measured multiplicity spectrum was used for
            absolute alpha normalization.
METHOD     (TOF)      Multiplicity spectrometry of gamma quanta
                      and neutrons. 26 m flight path.
FACILITY   (LINAC)
DETECTOR   (NAICR)  48 sectional detector on the base of Na-I(Tl).
               Scintillation volume is about 180 litres.
           Fission events detection efficiency about 99.8 %,
           capture - 96.8 % .
           Geometric efficiency about 98 % .
           B-10 n-gamma converter (0.27 g/cm**2 thick) was used to
           detect neutrons by 480-keV gamma quantum of B-10.
           Cs-137, Co-60, Cf-252 were used for validation of
           detection efficiency .
CORRECTION  For backgrounds.
HISTORY    (20091126C) Compiled at CJD .
ENDBIB              24
